HEADWORD: Rolling-pin
<hw>Roll"ing-pin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cylindrical
piece of wood or other material, with which paste or dough may be rolled
out and reduced to a proper thickness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rollway</ent>⟦br⟧
